{"_id": "18424454|None", "id": "18424454", "infons": {}, "passages": [{"infons": {"journal": "Hum. Mol. Genet.; 2008 Jul 15; 17(14) 2219-27. doi:10.1093/hmg/ddn122", "year": "2008", "article-id_pmc": "PMC2599947", "type": "title", "authors": "Levran O, O Hara K, Peles E, Li D, Barral S, Ray B, Borg L, Ott J, Adelson M, Kreek MJ", "section": "Title"}, "offset": 0, "text": "ABCB1 (MDR1) genetic variants are associated with methadone doses required for effective treatment of heroin dependence.", "sentences": [], "annotations": [{"id": "3", "infons": {"identifier": "5243", "type": "Gene", "ncbi_homologene": "55496"}, "text": "ABCB1", "locations": [{"offset": 0, "length": 5}]}, {"id": "4", "infons": {"identifier": "5243", "type": "Gene", "ncbi_homologene": "55496"}, "text": "MDR1", "locations": [{"offset": 7, "length": 4}]}, {"id": "5", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D008691", "type": "Chemical"}, "text": "methadone", "locations": [{"offset": 50, "length": 9}]}], "relations": []}, {"infons": {"type": "abstract", "section": "Abstract"}, "offset": 121, "text": "Methadone is a mu-opioid receptor agonist used for treating opiate dependence. The range of effective methadone doses is broad. Part of the large inter-individual variability in efficacy may be accounted for by genetic factors. Methadone is a substrate of the transporter P-glycoprotein (P-gp) 170 that is encoded by the ABCB1 (MDR1) gene. Thus, P-gp variants may play a role in methadone absorption and distribution. We assessed the association between ABCB1 polymorphisms and methadone dose requirements in 98 methadone-maintained patients. The stabilizing methadone doses were normally distributed with a mean and median dose of 160 mg/day (range 30-280 mg/day). Statistical analysis showed significant difference in genotype frequencies between the 'higher' (&gt;150 mg/day) and 'lower' (&lt; or =150 mg/day) methadone dose groups for single nucleotide polymorphism (SNP) 1236C&gt;T (rs1128503) (experiment-wise P = 0.0325). Furthermore, individuals bearing the 3-locus genotype pattern TT-TT-TT (rs1045642, rs2032582 and rs1128503) have an approximately 5-fold chance of requiring the 'higher' methadone dose, while individuals heterozygous for these three SNPs have an approximately 3-fold chance of stabilizing at the 'lower' methadone dose (point-wise P-value = 0.026). These data suggest that specific ABCB1 variants may have clinical relevance by influencing the methadone dose required to prevent withdrawal symptoms and relapse in this population.", "sentences": [], "annotations": [{"id": "30", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D008691", "type": "Chemical"}, "text": "Methadone", "locations": [{"offset": 121, "length": 9}]}, {"id": "31", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D009293", "type": "Disease"}, "text": "opiate dependence", "locations": [{"offset": 181, "length": 17}]}, {"id": "32", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D008691", "type": "Chemical"}, "text": "methadone", "locations": [{"offset": 223, "length": 9}]}, {"id": "33", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D008691", "type": "Chemical"}, "text": "Methadone", "locations": [{"offset": 349, "length": 9}]}, {"id": "34", "infons": {"identifier": "5243", "type": "Gene", "ncbi_homologene": "55496"}, "text": "P-glycoprotein", "locations": [{"offset": 393, "length": 14}]}, {"id": "35", "infons": {"identifier": "5243", "type": "Gene", "ncbi_homologene": "55496"}, "text": "P-gp", "locations": [{"offset": 409, "length": 4}]}, {"id": "36", "infons": {"identifier": "5243", "type": "Gene", "ncbi_homologene": "55496"}, "text": "ABCB1", "locations": [{"offset": 442, "length": 5}]}, {"id": "37", "infons": {"identifier": "5243", "type": "Gene", "ncbi_homologene": "55496"}, "text": "MDR1", "locations": [{"offset": 449, "length": 4}]}, {"id": "38", "infons": {"identifier": "5243", "type": "Gene", "ncbi_homologene": "55496"}, "text": "P-gp", "locations": [{"offset": 467, "length": 4}]}, {"id": "39", "infons": {"identifier": "MESH:D008691", "type": "Chemical"}, "text"